<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-10-21T18:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-10-21T18:36:00-05:00" n="428" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d428">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">812.51/661: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-10-21T17:00:00-06:36"><hi rend="italic">October 21,
                                        1921—5 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 10:35
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>196. Lamont reports failure of negotiations due to Government’s
                            insistence on attempting to carry out bond purchase clause of oil
                            agreement. However, door is left open for resumption of negotiations on
                            sound basis when Mexican authorities appreciate that bond purchase
                            proposal is not workable.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>